# Azure Deployment Plan for Heart Disease Prediction

## Goal
Deploy the complete project (frontend + Flask API) as a single Python Azure App Service so `/` serves the UI and `/api/*` serves backend endpoints.

## Project Information
- App name: Heart Disease Prediction
- Stack: Python Flask backend + static HTML/CSS/JS frontend
- Hosting model: Single service on Azure App Service (Linux, Python 3.12)
- Data dependency: `heart_disease_selected_features.csv` packaged with application

## Resource Architecture
```mermaid
graph TD
frontend[Frontend static files]
api[Flask API routes /api/*]
appsvc[Azure App Service Linux Python]
appinsights[Application Insights]

frontend --> appsvc
api --> appsvc
appsvc --> appinsights
```

## Recommended Azure Resources
- Azure App Service (Linux)
  - SKU: B1 (good for dev/test and light production traffic)
  - Runtime: Python 3.12
  - Startup command: `gunicorn --bind=0.0.0.0 --timeout 600 api.server:app`
- Azure App Service Plan (Linux)
  - SKU: B1
- Application Insights
  - SKU: Basic workspace-based

## Security and Config
- Keep secrets in App Service settings (not hardcoded in source)
- Enable HTTPS only
- Restrict CORS if frontend is later split to a separate origin

## Execution Steps
- [ ] Install Azure CLI if missing
- [ ] Log in with `az login`
- [ ] Run deployment script:
  - `powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .azure/deploy.ps1 -SubscriptionId <SUBSCRIPTION_ID> -ResourceGroup <RESOURCE_GROUP> -AppName <UNIQUE_APP_NAME> -Location centralindia`
- [ ] Validate deployment:
  - Open `https://<UNIQUE_APP_NAME>.azurewebsites.net`
  - Open `https://<UNIQUE_APP_NAME>.azurewebsites.net/api/health`

## Troubleshooting
- If deployment fails with runtime mismatch, verify Python runtime:
  - `az webapp list-runtimes --os linux | Select-String PYTHON`
- If zip deploy times out, rerun deploy command once (build step can be slow on first run)
